6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Canva and Snappa share a solid foundation of core features including Templates, Drag And Drop, Export Formats, Stock Assets. Where Canva pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Brand Kit and Ai Generation and Collaboration and Animations and Responsive and Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Canva holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 10/10, while Snappa scores 5/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Canva and Snappa offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Canva's free tier and Snappa's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
