a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Canva is best suited for non designers, social media managers, small businesses, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Snappa, meanwhile, shines for bloggers, social media managers, non designers, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2012, Canva describes itself as \"All-in-one visual design platform with AI-powered creation tools.\" Snappa, established in 2015, positions itself as \"Simple online graphic design tool for quick social media and marketing visuals.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Canva** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 5.0), more features (10 vs 4), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Snappa is a poor choice — far from it. Snappa excels in its own right, particularly for bloggers and social media managers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value incredibly easy to use for anyone, go with Canva. If very fast and simple to use matters more to you, Snappa is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
